Subject: Re: [VB] tranny drain plug trick

What I do is root around in the junk box for a 17mm
hex nut, then use a small 3-sided file to square out
the hole in the middle.  Then, you can slip it onto a
3/8" socket extension, put it on the ratchet, and go. 

 
    -Carl

--- Don Johnson <djohnson1(-at-)snet.net> wrote:
> For $1.16 I made a little tool today to get the
> drain and fill plugs out of my '65
> 
> 1 - 3" Automotive bolt with a 17mm head
> 2  17mm nuts
> 
> 
> The two nuts lock each other, so vise grips on the
> bottom one loosens, on the top
> one, tightens
> Not one flaps, or even VW dealer even knew what I
> was talking about
> when I asked about a 3/8 17mm hex socket.  The
> Foriegn Flaps guy said
> "you'll never find anything like that out here"
> (CT).  So I made this little thing and it's worked
> good so far. Will still order the socket from
> someone for safe re-tightening
> 
> Just thought I'd share my small triumph
> 
> Don
> 65 EZ
> 71 westy
